(1+2x)-2(1+2x+3x^2)+3(1+2x+3x^2+4x^3)-4(1+2x+3x^2+4x^3+5x^4)
By Combining like terms, we get that
\begin{align*}
(1+2x)-2(1+2x+3x^2)+3(1+2x+3x^2+4x^3)-4(1+2x+3x^2+4x^3+5x^4) &= -(6x^2+12x)+(-8x^2-8x)+(9x^2+24x+12x^3)\\
& \hspace{10em}- (20x^3+12x^2+40x) \\
& = -6x^2-12x-8x^2-8x+9x^2+24x+12x^3-20x^3-12x^2-40x \\
& = \boxed{-6x^2+(24x-40x)+(-12x-8x)+(-6x^2-12x^2-20x^3)+12x^3},
\end{align*}
which has zero in all other terms except $-12x$  and $12x^3$.
So, the answer is
\begin{align*}
-12x+12x^3 &= 0x+ \boxed{-12x}+12x^3 \\
\Rightarrow \text{ Coefficient of } \ x &= \boxed{-12}
\end{align*}
